The paper discusses the use of reinforcement learning for whole-body control of a mobile manipulator, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of end-to-end learning also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also mentions obstacle avoidance, which is a common topic in control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the validation of the learned policy on a physical robot suggests a potential application in computer vision (cs.CV) for perception and localization.
